ASABA – Delta State House of Assembly Aspirant for Ethiope West Constituency, Comrade Edafe Ofotokun, on Thursday tipped Governor Ifeanyi Okowa for a higher political office in 2023. Speaking on Thursday at the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Secretariat, Asaba, Comrade Ofotokun promised to give his constituents efficient representation if he is given their mandate. He said, “I aspire to serve the people of Ethiope West Constituency at the Delta State House of Assembly. If given the opportunity to serve, I would ensure purposeful representation and people-oriented programs. “The youths will be coordinated through a self-sustaining programme of entrepreneurship and the women will be grouped into cells of business support to exchange ideas and access business support stipends.” He expressed optimism over the chances of the PDP to retain power in Delta State by producing the next Governor of the State. He further mentioned that Governor Ifeanyi Okowa has the capacity for a higher elective office, saying that he can positively affect the lives of Nigerians. He lauded Governor, Senator Ifeanyi Okowa, leader of the party, Chief James Ibori and other stakeholders of the party for the cordial handling of party affairs. He then prayed for a peaceful and smooth transition of powers in 2023.